Disputes (Resolutions) Policy
Overview
Generally, transactions are conducted smoothly on Slrshoppee. However there may be some cases where both the Buyers and Sellers/shop entity may face issues. At Slrshoppee, we have a Dispute Resolution process in order to resolve disputes between Buyers and Sellers/shop entity.
What is a 'dispute'?
A 'Dispute' can be defined as a disagreement between a Buyer and a Seller/shop entity in connection with a transaction on the Platform.
How does a 'dispute' occur in the Marketplace?
Disputes are filed as a result of a disagreement between the Buyer and the Seller/shop entity. Disputes arise out of an issue that is raised by either party not being completely satisfied with the resolution of their complaint/issue.
It is important that before a Buyer/Seller/shop entity raises a dispute, they should attempt to solve the issue. Please note that whenever a Buyer raises a dispute, the Seller's/shop entity payment for that order is put on hold immediately until the issue is resolved.
How is a 'dispute' created?
Whenever there is a disagreement, the Buyer can contact us through this link https://www.slrshoppee.com/helpcentre, while the Seller can write to ss@slrshoppee.com, in order to raise a dispute. Disputes can be raised at a particular transaction level.
What are the various types of 'disputes'?
Following are the indicative examples of potential disputes:
9.	Wrong item received
10.	Item Not as described
11.	Damaged or Seal broken on Product
12.	Part/Accessory missing
13.	Item not Compatible
14.	Seller Description/Specification Wrong
15.	Defective (Functional issues)
16.	Product not working and Manufacturer claims invalid Invoice
In case the Seller/shop entity rejects the return request of the Buyer, and Buyer raises a dispute, then Slrshoppee will try to mediate and resolve the dispute between both the parties. If the dispute is resolved in favour of the Buyer, a refund is provided once the product is returned to the Seller/shop entity. If the dispute is settled in favour of the Seller/shop entity, Buyer is entitled to any refund.
Buyer Protection Program
In case of a dispute where the Seller/shop entity is unable to provide a refund or a replacement, Slrshoppee will actively work towards reaching a resolution.
The Buyer Protection Program covers Buyers who are unable to successfully resolve their dispute with the Seller/shop entity or are not satisfied the resolution provided by the Seller.
The buyer can contact us through this link https://www.slrshoppee.com/helpcentre if the issue with the Seller/shop entity is not resolved. Slrshoppee's Customer Support team will look into the case to check for possible fraud and if the Buyer has been blacklisted/blocked from making purchases on the Platform. Only after verifying these facts, a dispute can be registered.
Slrshoppee CS team will not facilitate a conference call, slrshoppeeCS team acts as the bridge between customer and seller/shop entity.
When a dispute has been raised, Slrshoppee may provide both the parties access to each others Display Names, contact details including email addresses and other details pertaining to the dispute. Buyers and Sellers/shop entity are subject to final consent from Slrshoppee for settling the dispute.
Buyer Eligibility and Restrictions
Only the Buyers who have purchased the product on Slrshoppee are eligible for the Buyer Protection Program.
Buyers can file a dispute within 45 days from the date of delivery of the product
Any damage or loss to the product after delivery will not be covered under this program and will completely be the Buyer's responsibility. Buyers should refuse to accept delivery if the item is damaged.
To be able to take advantage of the Buyer Protection Program, Buyers should first contact the Seller/shop entity and attempt to resolve the issue. If the Buyer doesn't hear from the Seller/shop entity or is unable to resolve the issue with the Seller/shop entity even after contact, a dispute can be raised with Slrshoppee by contacting us through the link: https://www.slrshoppee.com/helpcentre
Fraudulent charges and claims are not covered under Buyer Protection Program
If the Buyer has already initiated chargeback through the credit card issuing bank, it will not be covered under Buyer Protection Program, though in such cases a Seller can file a claim through the Seller Protection Program.
Blacklisted and Blocked Buyers are not covered by the Buyer Protection Program.
Buyers who have reached their maximum lifetime limit for claims are also not eligible. Buyers can make a maximum of 5 claims per year on Slrshoppee. If the claim was withdrawn, it is not counted. The coverage amount will be limited to rs 50,000
Through the Buyer Protection program, Slrshoppee does not provide any guarantee/warranty to Buyers for products sold on Slrshoppee against technical/manufacturing defects.
Raising disputes against Sellers does not automatically entitle the Buyer to a refund or replacement for the product purchased. Slrshoppee shall verify the disputes so raised and may process only such claims that are valid and genuine.
Slrshoppee shall at no point be responsible for any direct or indirect losses, expenses, costs of any nature whatsoever that may be incurred by any Buyer/Seller/shop entity.
Claims of the nature of 'Buyer remorse' (i.e. instances where products are bought by the Buyer by mistake or where the Buyer chooses to change his/her mind with regard to the product purchased by him) will not be entertained through this program.
Slrshoppee reserves its right to initiate civil and/or criminal proceedings against a User who, files an invalid and/or false claims or provides false, incomplete, or misleading information. In addition to the legal proceedings as aforesaid, Slrshoppee may at its sole discretion suspend, block, restrict, cancel the Display Name [and its related Display Names] of such User and/or disqualify that user and any related users from availing protection through this program.
Decisions made by Slrshoppee under the Buyer Protection Program shall be final and binding on its Users.
Slrshoppee reserves the right to modify / discontinue Buyer Protection Program without any prior notice period to its Users.
Through this program, Slrshoppee shall not entertain claims of Buyers who have incurred loss due to delayed shipment or delivery of the item by the Seller/shop entity.
Slrshoppee Customer Support Team may seek additional information / clarification from Buyer to facilitate resolution of the dispute. In the event Buyer does not respond with information / clarification sought within 10 days of such request, the dispute shall be auto-closed in favour of the Seller/shop entity.
